Warehouse Supervisor
29 Apr 2014 05:04 PM - UAE
. At DHL, people mean the world to us. That's why our goal has always been to attract and retain the best talent the world over. We provide challenge and opportunity for personal and professional development. We recognize the difference you bring to our business, and together we share the pride of building THE logistics company for the world.Working for DHL Global Forwarding means working for the global market leader in air and ocean freight.At DHL Global Forwarding, our expertise lies in the fast and flexible transportation of goods and merchandise across all continents. We not only supply comprehensive international logistic services, but also play an active role in reducing C02 emissions as seen in our GoGreen product portfolio.Warehouse SupervisorDHL Global Forwarding (DGF) manages the flow of goods and information across a customer's global supply chain utilizing air/ocean/ground transportation, customs brokerage services, and dedicated warehousing/distribution centers. We are part of Deutsche Post DHL, the world's leading logistics provider with operations in over 220 countries. Visit our career site on the web at www.dp-dhl-karriere.de/en/career.html.SummaryMonitors team of Storekeepers/Specialists and maintains smooth warehouse OperationsHandles cargo movement and performs loading and unloading of trucks/containers, complying with regulations and internal procedures; takes corrective actions, if requiredCoordinates processing of shipments and handling of physical documentsManages handling equipmentPlans resources and capacity (space, people)Tasks and AccountabilitiesMonitors daily operation of warehouseOwns staffing responsibility and training of contractorsAssures Quality Management Systems are implemented strictly and reports inactive QMS activities of his/her field of responsibilityPlans and organizes an efficient and effective functional department, adhering to regulations and internal proceduresDevelops IKOs/KPIs with team members and monitors individual performanceIdentifies training needs and opportunities to develop a highly skilled functional departmentMonitors subcontractor performance and develops improvement plan with subcontractor for rectification of performance issues in compliance with Company and DPWN Corporate policy and standardsEnsures contracted suppliers comply with company quality proceduresMaintains pro-active communication/relationship with peers/superiors and especially informs superior immediately of discrepancies, problems or non performance or non observanceCoordinates processing of shipments and handling of physical documentsManages handling equipmentQualificationsForklift operating and hand pallet truck operating skillsRelevant working safety regulation knowledgeUnderstanding of each customer's needsCapacity to set clear and realistic goals and objectivesLeadership and training skills to develop team membersShift work required: Day-time onlyJob function: Transportation & Warehouse ManagementCountry: United StatesReports to: Jim HolderPosition offered by: DHL Global Forwarding USContract: Permanent (Full-Time)Date: 28/04/14Travel required: No business travelsWork permit required: NoLocation: Texas (DFW Airport-DZ-DFW)Career level:
